entry.title: WEATHER ADVISORY , Killarney
entry.summary: Persons in or near this area should be on the lookout for adverse weather conditions and take necessary safety precautions. Issued: 5:07 PM EST Friday 24 February 2023

entry.title: Friday night: Increasing cloudiness. Low minus 23.
entry.summary: Clear. Increasing cloudiness after midnight. Wind up to 15 km/h. Low minus 23. Wind chill minus 21 this evening and minus 31 overnight. Risk of frostbite. Forecast issued 6:25 PM EST Friday 24 February 2023

entry.title: Saturday: Flurries at times heavy. High minus 7.
entry.summary: Flurries at times heavy ending in the afternoon then cloudy with 60 percent chance of flurries. Risk of snow squalls in the morning and early in the afternoon. Local amount 5 cm. Wind becoming east 20 km/h gusting to 40 in the morning then light early in the afternoon. High minus 7. Wind chill minus 32 in the morning and minus 10 in the afternoon. Risk of frostbite. UV index 1 or low. Forecast issued 6:25 PM EST Friday 24 February 2023

entry.title: Saturday night: Flurries. Low minus 10.
entry.summary: Cloudy. 60 percent chance of flurries in the evening. Flurries beginning late in the evening. Amount 2 to 4 cm. Wind becoming west 20 km/h gusting to 40 after midnight. Low minus 10. Wind chill minus 10 in the evening and minus 16 overnight. Forecast issued 6:25 PM EST Friday 24 February 2023
